We now invert this to express $(t', x')$ in terms of $(\tau, t_x)$.
Let the matrix be $M$, then $\det(M)$ is:

\begin{align}
\Delta &= (\cos\alpha)(\beta\cos\alpha) - (\beta\sin\alpha)(-\sin\alpha) \\
